name: Air Canada Express New Livery CRJ-900LR [C-FJZL] Taxi and Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
The latest aircraft type in Air Canada's fleet to receive their new livery is the CRJ-900LR! The second one to be painted as such is seen here taxiing up close on Bravo (with a very friendly crew) and taking off 17L en route to Houston on what I believe is the third or fourth visit of the new Air Canada Express livery. ATC is included, hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
